Maria Camila Restrepo-Ceron

About me

Im passionate about advancing health equity in population oral health through epidemiological methods. Im currently a Masters student in Epidemiology at Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School of Public Health, and I hold a Bachelors degree in Dentistry (BDS) from CES University in Medelln, Colombia.

My work integrates research and clinical practice, focusing on the intersection of social and oral health epidemiology, including conditions like cleft lip and palate. While pursuing my degree, I also work as a research assistant, coordinating community-based HIV research projects in Latino populations.

I also serve as president of the Latino Public Health Network student group and as Masters Co-Representative of the Epidemiology Student Organization (ESO) at JHSPH. My research collaborations include work with CES-LPH in Colombia and the Cariology Research Group at UT Health, San Antonio.

Education

Johns Hopkins University | Baltimore, MD

Master of Science (ScM) in Epidemiology | August 2023 - May 2025

Relevant coursework: Epidemiologic Methods, Biostatistics, Systematic Reviews and Meta-Analysis, Social Epidemiology and Health Equity, Global Health Economics and Economic Evaluation.

CES University | Medellin, Colombia

Bachelors degree in Dentistry (BDS) | Jan 2017 - Man 2022

Research Experience

University of Texas Health (UTHSCSA), San Antonio, TX | Research Internship | April 2024 - Present

Clinical Experience

Dental Clinic Enlace Dental, Medellin, Colombia | General dentist in private practice | Jan.2022 July 2023

State Social Enterprise (ESE) San Rafael Hospital, Girardota, Colombia | Internship in a rural state hospital | Sept.- Oct.2021

Publications
